<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran's Supreme National Security Council (SNSC)
issued a report Saturday night on the rally of Tehran University
students last month and the following clashes with police and
civilian opponents in the dormitory.
</P>
<P>
The report said an investigation committee set up by SNSC
found the Tehran University dorm incident on July 8-9 is
"completely separate" from ensuing demonstrations and street riots.
(BC-Iran-Report-Crackdown)
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak has instructed
the army to begin preparations for resuming implementation of the
Wye Memorandum on September 1, Israel Radio reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Prime Minister and Defense Minister Ehud Barak has told the
IDF (Israeli Defense Forces) to prepare to put in motion the
implementation of the Wye agreement at the beginning of September
1999. This means the land handover will begin on October 1," the
radio quoted a statement issued by the prime minister's office
late Saturday night as saying. (BC-Israel-Wye)
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak said Sunday he
is hopeful that Israeli and Palestinian negotiators will reach an
agreement in 10 days on the way of implementing the Wye accord.
</P>
<P>
"There is some kind of chance during the next 10 days that
some kind of agreement will be formulated on the manners in which
the Wye accord will be implemented," Israel Radio quoted Barak as
telling a weekly cabinet meeting. (BC-Israel-Wye)
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli police began an investigation Sunday into
a bomb explosion in the northern coastal city of Netanya which
they suspected to be a foiled major terror attack, Israel
television reports said.
</P>
<P>
Before the bomb exploded outside an office building in the
morning, the police spotted two men carrying suspicious packages,
the reports said. The men headed into downtown before police
could question them.
</P>
<P>
Security officials were quoted as saying that the suspects
might have intended to conduct the explosion in heavy traffic
areas but had to dump the bomb after realizing that they had been
spotted. (BC-Israel-Bombing) 
</P>
</TEXT>
