<HEADLINE> Kuwait Concerned Over Tension Between India and </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait on Sunday voiced
concern over the latest escalation of tension between India and
Pakistan and called on both sides to exercise self-restraint.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait's stance on the issue was defined during a regular
cabinet session chaired by Prime Minister Saad Al-Abdullah
Al-Sabah.
</P>
<P>
"The Council of Ministers followed with concern the escalation
of situation between India and Pakistan and its repercussions on
the stability of the region," said Deputy Prime Minister and
Minister of State for Cabinet Affairs and for National Assembly
Affairs Mohammad Deifallah Sharar after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait appealed to both states to exercise self-restraint and
resort to wisdom in solving their disputes.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan last Wednesday fired a surface-to-air missile toward
three Indian military helicopters over a marshy border where
India had shot down a Pakistani plane the day before.
</P>
<P>
The two air clashes in two days between the rival South Asian
neighbors came just weeks after the confrontation cooled down in
the disputed Kashmir region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
