<HEADLINE> Four Warships Join Kuwaiti Naval Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Naval Force was
joined on Sunday by four new warships, the first batch of
eight vessels Kuwait bought from France.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Deputy Prime Minister and Defense Minister Salem
Al-Sabah Al-Salem Al-Sabah, who inaugurated the ceremony, said
the gunships would "add a new shield to preserve the
security and stability of Kuwait."
</P>
<P>
The official Kuwait News Agency quoted Salem as saying that
the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait in 1990 had severely destroyed
the naval force, but "it did not stop Kuwait from rebuilding
its military installations."
</P>
<P>
It is in the interest of Kuwait to "always seek sophisticated
and top quality weapons," he said.
</P>
<P>
The four warships left France early last month and during
the journey took part in war games held with Tunisian naval
forces.
</P>
<P>
Commander of Kuwait's Naval Force, Rear-Admiral Ahmad Al-Mulla,
 said the 45-day journey and the war games were a good experience
for the crew.
</P>
<P>
Al-Mulla said the second batch of the French-made vessels
would arrive in Kuwait later this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
