<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Prepares National Anti-HIV/AIDS Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Health Ministry
have prepared a national program that enables it to prevent the
ever increasing spread of the HIV/AIDS pandemic in the country.
</P>
<P>
The five-year program, formulated in tune with the national
HIV/AIDS policy, will create a conducive atmosphere where HIV/AIDs
victims and AIDS orphans are cared for, Mengesha Yadeta, who is
working with HIV/AIDs and other sexually transmitted disease
control team, said at the weekend
</P>
<P>
The program will help religious institutions, governmental and
Non- governmental organizations as well as the public at large to
actively participate in the fight against the disease, Mengesha
said.
</P>
<P>
There are about three million HIV carriers in Ethiopia, the
expert said, adding that 68,966 HIV/AIDs cases had been reported
to various health institutions in the country over the last 13
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
