<HEADLINE> Lesotho Speaker dies in Accra </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NAIROBI, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Dr John Teboho Kolane,
Speaker of the National Assembly of Lesotho, was found dead in his
room at the Golden Tulip Hotel in Accra on Sunday morning, the
Ghana News Agency (GNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
 Dr Kolane, believed to be in his early seventies,
participated in the Commonwealth Parliamentary Association, Africa
Region Conference, which ended in Accra Friday.
