<HEADLINE> Italy Beats Greece to Win Men's Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, Croatia, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Italy defeated Greece 3-
2 in a well-matched final to win the men's volleyball title at the
Military World Games here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Italy, inspired by Best Player Award winner Hristo Slatanov,
took the first set 25-19 but could not stop the Greeks from
snatching the next two sets 26-24 and 25-22.
</P>
<P>
The Italians rallied to level the score by winning the crucial
fourth set 25-22 before sealing their victory with a 15-12 win in
the decider.
</P>
<P>
Greece's Vasilis Koyrnetas was named the Best Assistor while
the Best Attacker prize went to Dean Laninovic of Croatia.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's third-place play-off, Croatia beat South Korea 21-
25, 25-19, 28-16, 21-25, 15-11 in an equally tight game to grab
the bronze medal. 
