<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EDS-With Details China Reveals Misuse of 117.4 Billion Yuan (With Details) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 16 (Xinhua) -- China's audit departments have
found 117.4 billion yuan of money misused under the financial law,
and saved 15.3 billion yuan for the country in the first half of
this year, according to the country's top auditor.
</P>
<P>
Li Jinhua, auditor-general of China's National Audit Office,
told an ongoing national auditing meeting here today that the
audit departments also sent 297 cases of suspected economic crimes
to judicial departments, and assisted them in 317 such cases
during the first six months this year.
</P>
<P>
From October of last year to April of this year, the National
Audit Office audited the Finance Ministry's implementation of the
Central Government's budget, and found a delay in its work on the
budget, and a failure to put financial revenues into the national
treasury.
</P>
<P>
It then audited 15 provincial taxation administrations, and
found they had exceeded their power to reduce and relieve taxes,
and had allowed tax evasion.
</P>
<P>
During its audit of 18 Customs departments, it was revealed
that these departments reduced tariff rates in violation of State
regulations.
</P>
<P>
The National Audit Office also audited 18 provincial treasuries,
and found they had engaged in loose auditing practices regarding
revenues, and pocketed Central Government revenues into their own
accounts.
</P>
<P>
Notably, during its audit of 54 departments directly under the
State Council, it found many cases of the misuse of funds for
special projects, and failures to allocate money to designated
projects.
</P>
<P>
It also discovered that Tianjin's Jixian County Taxation Bureau
created fake invoices on value-added taxes, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Water Resources was found to have illegally
collect money to build luxury office buildings, and embezzled the
funds of water projects for other uses.
</P>
<P>
According to the top auditor, thus far the National Audit
Office has completed auditing 10 of the 14 cases specified by the
Central Government. It has also assisted related departments in
dealing with a bribery case involving major smuggling activities
in the city of Zhanjiang in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
