<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-16 15:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran's Detente Policy Serves National </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami Monday pledged to stick to the detente policy, saying it
best serves the country's security and interests.
</P>
<P>
Addressing heads of Iran's representative missions abroad,
Khatami said the policy is "based on guaranteeing, strengthening,
improving and stabilizing national security and interests."
</P>
<P>
A moderate cleric, Khatami was swept to power by overwhelming
popular support in the presidential election two years ago. He has
since been trying to ease tension with other countries, including
the United States, by proposing dialogs among civilizations.
</P>
<P>
This policy effectively broke Iran's isolation in the
world.
</P>
<P>
"By raising the idea of dialog among civilizations," the
president said, "Iran has invited the world to peace based on
justice, equality and elimination of force from international
relations."
</P>
<P>
"Detente does not mean being ignorant of threats," he was
quoted by the official Islamic Republic News Agency as
explaining, "rather it is aimed at identifying the borders of
enmity, strengthening friendships and commonalties and being aware
of threats."
</P>
<P>
He told the diplomats that a dialog among civilizations has
been an effort to improve ongoing relations at the global level.
</P>
<P>
On Iran's relations with neighbors in the Gulf, Khatami said
"Security in the Persian Gulf is in the interest of all. "
</P>
<P>
"We should maintain our vigilance and adopt wise methods in
order to confront temptations to foment tension and spark clashes
in the region," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said Iran's policy of detente will succeed if the people
enjoy better living standard.
</P>
<P>
Khatami asked the diplomats to make more efforts to influence
the world opinion and to remove the "horrible" distortion of Iran
by its enemies, mainly the U.S. and Israel.
</P>
<P>
He said Iran's foreign policy should be in tune with what is
going on within the country, adding Iran is in need of stability,
sework of law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
