<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BJP-Alliance to Bar Foreign Origin Persons Occupying High Posts in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The BJP-led National
Democratic Alliance (NDA) Monday said in its manifesto that it
will enact a law barring people of foreign origin from holding
high offices like that of prime Minister.
</P>
<P>
The proposal assumes significance in the context of Congress
President Sonia Gandhi's decision to enter the electoral fray and
the possibility of her becoming prime minister in case her party
is voted to power.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee said that the NDA would try
to evolve a consensus with other parties and implement the
proposal "at the earliest."
</P>
<P>
In a sharp reaction to the NDA agenda, a Congress spokesman
said it showed that the alliance was "afraid" of Sonia Gandhi and
had lost hopes of winning the elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
