<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Star Elliott Getting New Kidney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 16 (Xinhua) -- San Antonio Spurs star Sean
Elliott underwent a kidney transplant today in an operation that
was to take six hours.
</P>
<P>
Doctors began removing the healthy kidney from Elliott's
brother Noel this morning, said Palmira Arellano, a spokeswoman at
Methodist Specialty and Transplant Hospital in San Antonio.
</P>
<P>
Elliot needs a transplant to change his kidneys. The cause of
the disease is not clear.
</P>
<P>
Urologists Sammy Vick and Cliff Sarnecky were removing Noel's
kidney in a procedure expected to last three to four hours.
Surgeon Francis Wright was scheduled to perform the transplant in
a procedure taking four to six hours.
</P>
<P>
Elliot, 31, announced last month, a few weeks after the Spurs
won the NBA championship, that he was in need of a transplant.
</P>
</TEXT>
