<HEADLINE> Arafat Urges Exact Israeli Implementation of Wye </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) President Yasser Arafat on Monday called on Israel
to exactly and honestly carry out the Wye peace accord signed last
October.
</P>
<P>
The PNA "is not asking for the impossible, only the exact and
honest (Israeli) implementation" of the Wye accord, Arafat told
reporters after a meeting with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak in
Alexandria, 220 kilometers northwest of Cairo.
</P>
<P>
Arafat arrived in the Mediterranean port city earlier in the
day to brief Mubarak on the latest developments of the peace talks
between the Palestinians and Israel, especially their negotiations
on the implementation of the Wye agreement.
</P>
<P>
He left Alexandria after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Arafat expressed frustration with the difficulties Israel has
put in the implementation of the Wye deal.
</P>
<P>
"(Israeli Prime Minister Ehud) Barak says he is committed to
implementing the agreement, but at meetings we find they put
difficulties like the time table," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Wye accord obliged Israel to pull back troops from
another 13.1 percent of the West Bank in three phases.
</P>
<P>
Former Israeli hard-line Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
suspended the implementation in December after the first
withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
Barak has pledged to carry out the accord and agreed to a
further 5 percent withdrawal beginning October 1.
</P>
<P>
But he calls for delaying the last pullback from 6 percent of
the West Bank until February 2000.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians have vehemently rejected the offer, and want
the pullout wrapped up by mid-November.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, a frequent visitor to Egypt, keeps close consultations
with Mubarak, who as the president of the first Arab country to
sign a peace treaty with Israel, plays an active role in mediating
the Mideast peace talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
