<HEADLINE> Tajikistan Blames Uzbekistan for Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The Tajik Foreign Ministry on
Monday handed a note to Uzbek Ambassador Bakhtiyar Urdashev
protesting the alleged bombing of Tajik villages by Uzbek military
aircraft on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Four Uzbek military planes bombed the Tajik territory in the
vicinity of a Khait village along with villages Gushkaba and
Tandikul, said the Tajik Foreign Ministry's Information Department
chief, Igor Sattarov.
</P>
<P>
There were no human casualties in the bombing, but buildings
were destroyed and 111 heads of cattle were killed. Crops were
lost in a subsequent fire on several hectares, the Interfax news
agency quoted Sattarov as saying in Dushanbe, the Tajik capital.
</P>
<P>
Tajik Foreign Minister Talbak Nazarov and Urdashev discussed
this "unprecedented fact" earlier on Monday, Sattarov said.
</P>
<P>
Nazarov expressed perplexity over "the absolutely unjustified
action of the Uzbek Air Force" and requested Tashkent to take
immediate steps to avert similar actions in the future. This
incident runs counter to the existing bilateral relations,
Sattarov said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
