<HEADLINE> World's Largest Rigid PVC Film Producer Comes on Line in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The world's largest rigid PVC
film production line became operational today in a plastic company
in this capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The Han Rigid Plastics Corp. has made itself a world class
company by installing new equipment with a monthly capacity to
turn out 4,500 tons of PVC film a month, which is mainly used for
making high-quality plastics for packaging, stationery products,
and building and decoration materials.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan-funded company is the producer of 70 percent of the
adhesive plaster used for making artificial Christmas trees
worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The company intends to add 100 million U.S. dollars of
investment to increase its annual output to 120,000 tons and
become the world's largest PVC producer. It has also been
investing in developing its own end-products such as electroplate
and printing and credit card materials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
