<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights of
the diplomatic news released by Xinhua today:
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao Meets Ecuadorean Guests
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
met with a delegation of the Popular Democracy Party of Ecuador
here Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadorean delegation, led by Ramiro Rivera Molina,
president of the Ecuador Popular Democracy Party, arrived are here
as guests of the International Department of the CPC Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
China and Ecuador have witnessed a smooth growth of bilateral
relations since the forging of diplomatic ties nearly two decades
ago, and bilateral exchange and cooperation in the political,
economic and cultural sectors have kept increasing, Hu, also vice-
president, noted.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his appreciation and gratitude toward the
Ecuadorean government for its principled stance of upholding the "
one China" policy and not having any official relations with
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"China highly values the friendly, cooperative relations with
Ecuador, and is ready to push forward the long-term, stable,
friendly and cooperative relations into the 21st century on the
basis of the five principles of peaceful co-existence," the
Chinese vice-president said.
</P>
<P>
 NPC Vice-Chairman Meets Israeli Visitors
</P>
<P>
Xu Jialu, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), met here today with a delegation
from the Israeli Public Council for Exchange of Youth and Young
Adults (IPCEYYA) headed by Elchanan Glatt, president of the
IPCEYYA.
</P>
<P>
Xu and the visitors exchanged views on furthering exchanges
between the Chinese and Israeli youth.
</P>
<P>
Xu said that the friendly relations between the youth of China
and Israel are an important part of the two countries' relations.
</P>
<P>
