<HEADLINE> Registration For UPU Congress Begins in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- International participants at
the 22nd Congress of the Universal Postal Union (UPU) to be held
in Beijing between August 23 and September 15 began to register at
the meeting today.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Jinshu, a Congress official in charge of registration,
said that more than 30 delegates from over a dozen countries and
international organizations registered today. Among these are
delegates from South Africa, New Zealand, Pakistan, Lesotho,
Canada, and the UPU.
</P>
<P>
Zheng said that it takes only several minutes to register a
participant who has already entered his or her name for the
meeting. She said it will take less than 15 minutes to register a
participant whose name is not pre-entered.
</P>
<P>
Kuai, a Chinese staff member who swiftly operates her computer
keyboard to register participants, said she felt excited about her
first working day at the registration desk. She said that thanks
to the fine training given by the Chinese Organizing Committee,
she had gotten off to a smooth start.
</P>
<P>
Zheng said that most participants are expected to register on
August 21 and 22 before the meeting opens. Registration for the
meeting will prolong working hours to 12-13 hours a day during
that period.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 2,200 people from 170 countries and 31
international organizations have entered their names as intended
participants. 
