huge market for Cambodia, Sithea San, head of the airline
commercial division said.
</P>
<P>
According to a report of the Ministry of Tourism, more than 12,
000 people from China (excluding Hong Kong) arrived in Cambodia by
air in the first half of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The figure is equal to 68 percent of the number of the visitors
from China in all of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Sithea San attributed the boost of Chinese visitors to a
Cambodia-China bilateral agreement on tourism signed in Beijing in
February. 
