<HEADLINE> China Reveals Misuse of 117.4 Billion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 16 (Xinhua) -- China's audit departments have
found 117.4 billion yuan of money misused under the financial law,
and saved 15.3 billion yuan for the country in the first half of
this year, according to the country's top auditor.
</P>
<P>
Li Jinhua, head of China's National Audit Office, told a
ongoing national auditing meeting here today that the audit
departments also sent 297 cases of suspected economic crimes to
judicial departments, and assisted them in 317 such cases during
the first six months this year.
</P>
<P>
From October of last year to April of this year, the National
Audit Office audited 15 provincial taxation administrations, 18
Customs departments, and 54 departments directly under the State
Council, finding that they abused their authority or position in
various forms, resulting in the misuse of more than 117 billion
yuan. 
</P>
