<HEADLINE> Kenyan Vice-President Calls for National Unity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The vice-president made the remarks Sunday at Keringeti
Secondary School of Nakuru District in central Kenya when he
presided over a fund-raising in aid of the school, the East
African Standard newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Saitoti urged the general public to foster harmonious
co-existence irrespective of their political persuasion and ethnic
background.
</P>
<P>
He also called on local leaders to always preach peace and
unity and to set a good example for the youth to emulate.
</P>
<P>
On agriculture, the vice-president urged local farmers to fully
utilize their land, saying the area was suitable for a variety of
cash crops,  besides livestock farming.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the government will protect local farmers
and  industries from cheap imports which deprived farmers of
their livelihood and jobs due to the collapse of local industries.
 
</P>
