<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Close 25,800 Small Coal Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- China plans to shut down 25,800
small coal mines nationwide by the end of this year, in a bid to
cut coal production and stockpiles and make the industry
profitable.
</P>
<P>
According to the China State Administration of Coal Industry,
coal supply exceeds demand by a big margin, while most of the
small mines continue random mining of coal resources.
</P>
<P>
To turn loss into profit in the coal sector, China has so far
closed down about 24,000 small coal mines.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, large state-owned collieries, the backbone of the
coal industry, have taken effective steps to produce according to
market demand, adjust their product mix, and lower production
costs.
</P>
<P>
Remarkable results have been scored in major coal-producing
provinces of Shanxi, Henan, Hebei, Heilongjiang, Sichuan and
Shaanxi, and the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region. The coal sector
expects to turn profitable by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
A senior coal official noted that China plans to slash coal
production by a total of 250 million tons this year, reducing
annual output to around 1.1 billion tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
