<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices recovered some of
their last trading day's losses on the Singapore Stock Market
Monday under the strong support from Wall Street and other Asian
bourses.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) earned 28.91 points to
end at 1998.59 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume was 145.92 million shares valued at 313.27
million Singapore dollars (about 184.27 million U.S. dollars).
Falls outnumbered rises by 139 to 145 with 161 counters unchanged
</P>
<P>
Gen Int was the most active stock with a turnover of 9.40
million units. AFP came second with 8.48 million shares done.
Hotung was the next with 6.95 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Both SPH and SPH 100 topped the actives chart climbing by 60
cents to end at the same 28.50 Singapore dollars. DBS, DBS F and
OUB F edged up 40 cents to finish at 17.80, 20.40 and 8.00
Singapore dollars respectively. NatElec and PacCent went up 35
cents to end at 7.75 and 6.25 Singapore dollars separately.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Thai Pr led losers of the day losing 25 cents
to close at 5.05 Singapore dollars. JurShip sank 20 cents to
finish at 7.35 Singapore dollars. F&AMP;N retreated 15 cents to end at
6.35 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the gains were also due to a technical
rebound following losses last week.
</P>
<P>
But they added that volume was low and trading was range-bound,
with shares slipping on profit-taking later in the day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
