<HEADLINE> Australia's Wine Exports Top Target Earlier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Australia's wine industry
Monday announced it had passed its 1-billion-Australian dollar
(660 million U.S. dollars) export target 17 months ahead of
schedule.
</P>
<P>
The industry in 1991 launched an export drive aiming to achieve
1 billion Australian dollars in overseas sales by December, 2000.
</P>
<P>
Australian Winemakers' Federation President Brian Croser told
reporters that the industry was shipping more than 670,000 bottles
overseas a day, with almost half the exports bound for the United
Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
Croser said Australia still only held less than four percent of
the world market share and the industry's aim for the next 50
years was to become the world's major quality wine exporter.
</P>
<P>
"We have enough vines in the ground to achieve this," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
