<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 400 Chechen Rebels Said Killed in Dagestan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Russian authorities said Monday
that federal forces have killed more than 400 militants in its
campaign to root out Islamic gunmen that infiltrated several
Dagestani villages near the breakaway Chechnya republic.
</P>
<P>
Federal troops have also destroyed three tanks, seven anti-
aircraft systems, five mortars, and four trucks carrying
ammunition for the rebels, who are believed to be commanded by
Chechen warlord Shamil Basayev.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 14 cars, five of which with militants inside, and
a busload of militants were also attacked during the operation in
the mountainous villages in the southern Russian republic, the
Interfax news agency reported, quoting the government press center
in Makhachkala, the regional capital.
</P>
<P>
The government offensive is believed to have caused panic among
the militants and prompted serious differences between Basayev and
Khattab, his Arab advisor known only by his last name and
reportedly came from Jordan or Saudi Arabia, Interfax said,
quoting Russian officers.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen sneaked into Dagestan on August 7 and seized several
villages. Russia's federal forces have since launched several
operations against the militants, using fighter aircraft,
helicopters and heavy mortars. Elite police squads and local
volunteers armed by the government also took part in the fighting.
</P>
</TEXT>
