<HEADLINE> BJP-Alliance to Try for Consensus on CTBT in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 16 (Xinhua) -- India's Prime Minister Atal
Bihari Vajpayee Monday said that the BJP-led National Democratic
Alliance will try to evolve a consensus on the issue of signing
the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT) even after its victory in
the coming elections.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held here following the release of the
manifesto of the BJP-alliance, he said, "We have already stated
that on signing CTBT there has to be a broad national consensus.
We are trying to evolve a consensus."
</P>
<P>
"After the elections a final decision will be taken in this
regard," he added.
</P>
<P>
Referring to a question about talks with Pakistan, he said, "A
meeting ground will have to be found. Our efforts will be directed
in that direction."
</P>
<P>
In his Independence Day address to the nation, Vajpayee ruled
out the possibility of resuming talks with Pakistan untill it
stopped sponsoring cross-border terrorism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
