<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Conference on Operational Research Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The 15th Conference of the
International Federation of Operational Research Societies, (IFORS)
which has attracted more than 1,000 Chinese and foreign experts
and scholars, opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Those attending the conference will exchange latest research
findings and developments in operational research, research on
management and decision-making, and other relevant research fields.
</P>
<P>
Operations research is a young field mainly concerned with ways
to make maximum use of limited resources, and the most efficient
operational procedures. It is closely related to social,
industrial, and military sciences.
</P>
<P>
China began operations research in late 1950s, and research
divisions have been established at the Institute of Mechanics and
the Institute of Mathematics under the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
The International Federation of Operational Research Societies
(IFORS), founded in 1959, is an international non-governmental
organization with 44 member societies. The China Operations
Research Society (CORS) joined the IFORS in 1982.
</P>
<P>
The 15th IFORS conference, sponsored by CORS, has received more
than 1,300 papers from over 50 countries.
</P>
<P>
"Operations Research has been widely applied to industrial and
agricultural activities in China, and has helped with
governmental high-level decision-making for the country's
sustainable development of the economy and the environment," said
Xu Guanhua, vice minister of Science and Technology.
</P>
<P>
"This research will provide deeper insights and better
understanding of global issues such as economic development,
population, and ecology and environment in the new millennium," Xu
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
