<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Set Up Micro-Electronic Research Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 16 (Xinhua) - Thailand will set up a new
micro-electronic research center to facilitate the development of
the industry in the country, Science, Technology and Environment
Minister Arthit Urairat said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said the center will also found a fundament for the
country's long-term economic growth and prosperity, the Thai News
Agency (TNA) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The proposed center is expected to bring to the country over
100 billion baht (2.7 billion U.S. dollars) compared to its
investment of 1.5 billion baht (40.5 million dollars), TNA quoted
the minister as saying.
</P>
<P>
The center, by becoming a multi-purpose facility to do
research, design and development work, will also become a
"springboard" for a chain development of microchip,
micro-electronic and electronic equipment businesses, the minister
said.
</P>
<P>
Arthit said he would submit the proposed plan to the cabinet in
the next two weeks for further consideration and final approval.
</P>
</TEXT>
