<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Navy Sinks 2 Rebel Boats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan navy gun boats
attacked a flotilla of Tamil rebel craft in the northeast of the
country Monday and sank two boats, media sources here said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the navy gun boasts detected the rebel boats
off the coast of Pulmoddai and began attacking them in a sea
battle that lasted several hours.
</P>
<P>
A civilian fisherman was killed and another injured and
admitted to a hospital at Padaviya town.
</P>
<P>
The rebel boats exploded just as they were hit by the navy
attacks, indicating they were carrying ammunition, a navy
spokesman was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The navy confirmed two rebel boats were sunk and three others
damaged, said the sources, adding that the casualties of the
rebels were not immediately known.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
island country since 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
