<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Build More Drug Rehabilitation Centers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua)-- China plans to set up drug
rehabilitation centers in 742 counties within the next three years,
according to Jia Chunwang, director of National Narcotics Control
Commission.
</P>
<P>
Jia, also Minister of Public Security, pointed out that the
final solution to the narcotics problem in China is to get rid of
the drug consuming markets.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, China had about 600,000 registered
drug addicts, eight times the number in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Jia called on all provinces, autonomous regions, and
municipalities to allocate more funds for drug rehabilitation
programs and speed up the construction of drug rehabilitation
centers.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that all compulsory rehabilitation centers are
subject to the management and supervision of local public security
bureaus, while all labor rehabilitation centers should be built
and monitored by judicial departments and voluntary rehabilitation
centers be controlled by local health departments.
</P>
<P>
Jia also urged the localities to improve the existing drug
rehabilitation centers and immediately outlaw the illicit ones.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
