<HEADLINE> BJP-Led Alliance Ensures Stable Government in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 16 (Xinhua) -- India's BJP-led National
Democratic Alliance (NDA) Monday promised to take steps for
ensuring a fixed term of five years for all elected bodies
including Lok Sabha and state legislatures.
</P>
<P>
The manifesto released by the NDA sought to free the country of
the triple curses of hunger, fear and corruption and transform it
into a new India that is prosperous, strong, self-confidence and
at peace with itself and the world.
</P>
<P>
The manifesto said in the present world it was of paramount
importance that India constantly maintain and strengthen the state
of preparedness, morale and combat effectiveness of its armed
forces.
</P>
<P>
Referring to international relations, the manifesto promised to
promote and strengthen regional groupings on the lines of SAARC
and ASEAN and re-orient the country's foreign policy to pursue
economic, commercial and security goals.
</P>
<P>
Attempts to build a system of trade and economic cooperation
through an expanded global system of trade preferences among
developing countries would be strongly supported, it said, adding
that national interest would be "more robustly" asserted at the
forthcoming conference of the WTO. 
</P>
