<DOCNO> XIE19990816.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gullit Vows to Make Newcastle Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Newcastle United manager Ruud
Gullit vowed on Monday that he would not be resigning from the
position.
</P>
<P>
The Dutchman appeared uncertain about his future in a post-
match interview following Sunday's 4-2 defeat at Southampton,
which left the Magpies bottom of the Premiership.
</P>
<P>
But after a discussion on the team bus back to the airport for
the flight to Tyneside, Gullit received the backing of the
Newcastle team and board. "I thought I might have lost the support
of the board, the fans and the players - but they have been good
enough to support me," Gullit said.
</P>
<P>
"But I really believe in this team and if they all support me,
which it appears they are, and give me the time I honestly believe
that I can make this team work.
</P>
<P>
"People should bear in mind that we have nine major injuries to
first-team squad members at this time. When everybody is fit I
really believe that this team can work."
</P>
<P>
Newcastle chairman Freddie Shepherd and chief executive Freddie
Fletcher have both given Gullit their total support.
</P>
<P>
Gullit's comments followed an interview immediately after the
defeat at The Dell which meant Newcastle had suffered their worst
start to a campaign in 40 years.
</P>
<P>
Asked on Sky Sports if he would consider resigning, he replied:
"You never know." When asked if he would be manager next week
against Wimbledon at St James' Park, he said: "I will have to
think about it. I will think about what I saw today and what I've
seen for the last few weeks."
</P>
<P>
Two goals from Hassan Kachloul and one each for Marian Pahars
and Mark Hughes condemned the Geordies to their third defeat of
the new season after Alan Shearer had fired them in front from the
penalty spot.
</P>
<P>
Gary Speed claimed a late consolation, but the Saints could
have had another from recent signing Trond Soltvedt who went close.
</P>
</TEXT>
