<HEADLINE> Macao Telecom Promotes School Internet Access </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Telecommunications
Company (CTM) plans to provide equipment, free Internet access and
technical support to local middle schools to help them make better
use of the latest information technology.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the company said that the project will promote the
sharing of knowledge and experience among schools, teachers and
students.
</P>
<P>
CTM will provide schools with required hardware, software and
installation service to ensure that they have high speed access to
the Internet. An expert Webmaster will assist schools to convert
existing teaching materials and other data to web pages.
</P>
<P>
The company plans to link all education home pages in Macao so
as to organize better online education. In addition, there will be
online discussion areas to facilitate communication between
schools.
</P>
<P>
CTM also considers running online workshops and competitions to
allow students to learn and produce innovative web pages. And
relevant training will enable teachers to design and produce
educational web pages and give them a better understanding of
Internet security and ethics. 
</P>
