<HEADLINE> Chinese Railways Earn 57 billion Yuan In First Seven Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- China's railway departments earned
57.7 billion yuan (6.89 billion dollars) in the first seven months
of 1999, according to the Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry reports that Chinese trains carried a total of 903
million tons of cargo and 571 million passengers during the period.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate a daily average of 2.85 million people were
transported in July. Included were 717,000 long-distance journeys,
up 17.5 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The amount of containers transported by rail stood at 305,000
TEUs (20-foot equivalent units) or 2.68 million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
