<HEADLINE> Share Prices Soar in Tokyo on Wall Street Surge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices rose sharply in Tokyo
Monday with the key Nikkei index closing at an almost two-week
high, following a surge on Wall Street last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange jumped 390.86 points, or 2.24
percent, from last Friday's close to end at 17,826.03.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, added 26.02 points or 1.80 percent to 1,468.
51.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 378.53 million
shares from 455.10 million shares last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba Corp. was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the sharp rise in the index stemmed from Wall
Street's strong performance and a rise in the futures price index
in Chicago on Friday, adding that technology issues in Tokyo
attracted active buying, boosted by their higher U.S. counterparts.
</P>
<P>
The key market gauge, however, lost upward momentum toward the
end of trading, due mainly to profit-taking after the rapid gain,
they said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outpaced
losers 995 to 205, with 97 issues ending unchanged.  
</P>
</TEXT>
