<HEADLINE> Post Office Expands Newspaper Distribution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Post offices around the country
have signed distribution contracts with more than 6,000 publishers
of newspapers and magazines in the country, according to
statistics released by the State Post Bureau today.
</P>
<P>
Post offices now distributed some 60 percent of Chinese
newspapers and periodicals.
</P>
<P>
The bureau has more than 40,000 offices for newspaper
subscription and more than 20,000 newsstands around the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics, the number of newspapers and
magazines that post offices distribute has increased from 262 to 6,
172 over the past five decades. The total circulation skyrocketed
to 21 billion from 400 million over the period.
</P>
<P>
A bureau official said that the well established postal network
around the country is ideal for newspaper distribution.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two decades since China began to reform and open
up to the outside world, post offices have begun to offer a series
of new services, including on-line subscription and express
delivery.
</P>
<P>
Postal distribution offices in 31 provinces, autonomous regions
and municipalities have already hooked up with a national computer
system, which links over 90 percent of the total number of such
offices in the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
