<DOCNO> XIE19990816.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Makes Major Breakthrough in Oil Exploration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The Dagang Oilfield, a
subsidiary of the China National Petroleum Corp (CNPC) has found a
large oil and gas field in Guqianshan near the port city of
Tianjin in north China, with oil resources forecast at 100 million
tonnes.
</P>
<P>
"This is a significant breakthrough in onshore oil and gas
exploration in the eastern part of China ", said a CNPC official
today.
</P>
<P>
Guqianshan has an oil-and gas-bearing area of 60 square
kilometers. A total of 15 oil- and gas-bearing blocks have been
drilled in the recent exploration which adopted the latest
technologies.
</P>
<P>
Rich oil and gas flows have been found in the No.7, 8 and 4
wells in the Guqianshan exploration area.
</P>
<P>
The most important finding has been in the No.7 well. With
thickness of oil layer extending 100 meters, the well has a daily
oil and gas output of 609 cubic meters and 454,000 cubic meters,
respectively, equivalent to 1,000 tonnes of crude in total.
</P>
<P>
The Dagang Oilfield, launched in 1964, has developed an annual
oil production capacity of over four million tonnes, and has
produced cumulatively 100 million tonnes of crude oil so far.
</P>
<P>
However, through 30 years of exploration, the proven oil
reserves here are on the decline.
</P>
<P>
To maintain sustainable oil development in the next century,
the oilfield has blazed new trails and introduced lots of advanced
technologies from abroad, which helped it broaden exploration
areas.
</P>
<P>
The success in oil and gas exploration in Guqianshan will
provide references for exploration in similar geological
structures in the Bohai Bay areas, said the CNPC official.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
