<HEADLINE> Kenyan Vice-President Against Legalizing Abortion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan Vice-President George
Saitoti has said that abortion should never be legalized, claiming
that it is against the sanctity and dignity of human life.
</P>
<P>
The Daily Nation newspaper Monday quoted Saitoti as saying that
abortion was acceptable only when a mother's life was endangered
by a fetus.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Julius Meme, chief civil servant in Kenyan
Health Ministry, called for legalizing abortion, which triggered a
growing row over the issue.
</P>
<P>
Meme contended that existing laws on abortion were colonial and
 too strict in the modern society.
</P>
<P>
He said legalizing abortion would save women from shying away
from help with doctors and therefore secure their lives and
health.
</P>
<P>
Legalizing abortion has encountered strong opposition from the
Catholic Church, which has many followers in Kenya.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
