<HEADLINE> Vietnam Makes Progress in Afforestation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has planted 154,700
hectares of forests in the first seven months of this year, a
year-to-year increase of 3.34 percent, the Vietnam News Agency
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
In July alone, 25,200 hectares of concentrated forests were
planted and 35,000 more hectares were rehabilitated, according to
Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development reports.
</P>
<P>
More than 5,000 hectares were forested by aerial seeding in
remote and mountainous areas of the country's northwestern
province of Lai Chau, with survival rate ranging between 80 and 90
percent.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam is carrying out a program to plant 5 million hectares
of forests by the year 2010, thus raising forest coverage to 43
percent from nearly 30 percent at present.
</P>
<P>
The country plans to grow 310,000 hectares of forests this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
