<DOCNO> XIE19990816.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Southern African Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The heads of state or government
of the 14- member Southern African Development Community (SADC)
are jetting in Maputo, capital of Mozambique, for their 19th
summit on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The leaders will prepare their countries and the region for the
 approaching new millennium by pursuing peace and stability in
southern Africa and promoting regional integration.
</P>
<P>
The organization, originally known as the Southern African
Development Coordination Conference (SADCC), was formed in Zambian
capital Lusaka on April 1, 1980, when nine founding member states
adopted the Lusaka Declaration -- Southern Africa: Toward Economic
Liberation.
</P>
<P>
On August 17, 1992, the SADCC member states signed a treaty
establishing the Southern African Development Community, which
replaced the SADCC.
</P>
<P>
The treaty places binding obligations on member countries, with
the aim of promoting economic integration toward a fully developed
common market.
</P>
<P>
Now the SADC has 14 members: Angola, Botswana, the Democratic
Republic of the Congo, Lesotho, Malawi, Mauritius, Mozambique,
Namibia, Seychelles, South Africa, Swaziland, Tanzania, Zambia and
Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
The community offers world trade, industry and investment
opportunities in a regional market of 199 million people with a
gross domestic product of 176 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The 14 members are scheduled to begin tariff reduction from
January 1, 2000 aiming to eventually achieve a SADC free trade
area within five years.
</P>
<P>
Other objectives of the community include: achieving
development and economic growth, alleviating poverty, enhancing
the standard and quality of life of the peoples of southern Africa
and supporting the socially- disadvantaged through regional
integration.
</P>
<P>
Committed to promote and defend peace and security, the SADC is
also aiming to evolve common political values, systems and
institutions by strengthening and consolidating the long-standing
historical, social and cultural affinities and links among the
peoples of the region.
</P>
<P>
In order to promote self-sustaining development on the basis of
 collective self-reliance and the inter-dependence of member
states, the organization has to harmonize political and
socio-economic policies and plans of member states.
</P>
<P>
Through mobilizing the peoples and their institutions to take
initiatives to develop economic, social and cultural ties across
the sub- region and to participate fully in the implementation of
the common programs and projects, the SADC can help achieve
complementarity between national and regional strategies.
</P>
<P>
Facing the looming challenges created by the globalization
process, the SADC shall promote the development of human resources
in the region and promote the development, transfer and mastery of
technology.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the organization shall also manage to secure
international understanding, cooperation and support, mobilize the
inflow of both public and private resources into the sub-region.
</P>
<P>
The 19th SADC summit is set to elect its new chairman.
</P>
<P>
Current SADC chairman is South African President Thabo Mbeki
who took the chair of the regional organization after winning the
June 2 election this year.
</P>
<P>
Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano is the vice-chairman of
the organization. He is believed to be elected as the new
chairman at the Maputo summit.
</P>
<P>
Kaire Mbuende is the SADC executive secretary.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters of the community is located in Botswanan
capital Gaborone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990816.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Meets Ecuadorean Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee and state vice-president, met
with a delegation of the Popular Democracy Party of Ecuador here
Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadorean delegation, led by Ramiro Rivera Molina,
president of the Ecuador Popular Democracy Party, arrived are here
as guests of the International Department of the CPC Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
China and Ecuador have witnessed a smooth growth of bilateral
relations since the forging of diplomatic ties nearly two decades
ago, and bilateral exchange and cooperation in political, economic
and cultural sectors have kept increasing, Hu noted.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his appreciation and gratitude toward the
Ecuadorean government for its principled stance of upholding the "
one China" policy and not developing official relations with
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"China highly values the friendly, cooperative relations with
Ecuador, and is ready to push forward the long-term, stable,
friendly and cooperative relations into the 21st century on the
basis of the five principles of peaceful co-existence," the
Chinese vice-president said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Hu noted, the CPC will continue to work with the
Popular Democracy Party of Ecuador to strengthen the friendly
relations between the two parties.
</P>
<P>
Rivera said that China is a nation, which is economically
prosperous, politically stable and with sound social development
and openness to the outside world. He praised the country for the
role it has played as a "respectable and responsible big nation"
in the Asian and world affairs.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that Ecuador has similarities with China in its
foreign policy as it, too, upholds independence, self-
determination, peaceful co-existence and mutual respect among the
nations, and opposes any form of hegemony.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadorean people have always taken the Chinese people as
friends and are willing to continue the friendly cooperation with
China on the basis of equality and mutual respect, he said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Ecuadorean president said his party "respects
and admires" the CPC, and is willing to further advance the
friendship and cooperation between the two parties. 
</P>
