<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-16 08:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunt for Kidnapers Goes on: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 16 (Xinhua) -- A manhunt is going on for the
kidnapers of four foreign tourists and their Iranian guide in
the southern province of Kerman, according to the Iran Daily
newspaper here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Three men and two women armed with automatic weapons abducted
the five hostages from their Kerman hotel. The three Spanish
tourists, two of them priests, were identified as Pedro Garcia,
Joaquin Fernandez and Cosme Puerto, and the Italian captive Mas
simo Cattabriga.
</P>
<P>
The Identity of the Iranian guide is unknown.
</P>
<P>
"The security forces have sealed the roads into Kerman province
and have been mobilized to hunt for the kidnapers by helicopter,"
the paper quoted Abbas Doagooie, director general of political and
security affairs of Kerman province's governorate general, as
saying.
</P>
<P>
He said the kidnapers "are bandits and drug traffickers who
shift back and forth between the Iranian and Pakistani border
areas." In a major operation last Wednesday, security forces
killed four bandits and injured one, who was arrested.
</P>
<P>
"We have hit them hard in the past few months and they probably
retaliated by taking tourists as hostages," Doagooie said.
</P>
<P>
Kerman is known as a transit route for shipment of narcotics
from the "Gold Crescent" overlapping parts of Iran, Pakistan and
Afghanistan to European markets. Three Italians had been kidnaped
in the province in June. They were released a week later after
Interior Ministry intervened to negotiate with the abductors.
</P>
<P>
"We do not think that the act (kidnaping) was politically
motivated. We do not consider the abduction to be linked to the
Afghan crisis either," Doagooie said. Iran supports the Afghan
opposition called Northern Alliance against the ruling Taliban
regime.
</P>
<P>
Local media called the kidnaping as targeting Iran's security,
foreign and domestic investment as well as Iran's international
image, and urged security apparatus to find the root cause of the
problem and solve it as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Ministry on Sunday condemned the kidnaping,
calling it an "inhuman and ugly" act. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
