<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Consumer Price Index Up by 3.1 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's consumer price
index (CPI) for the period from January to July 1999 increased by
3.1 percent over that of the same period last year, the Statistics
Department said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 3.1-percent increase in the CPI, a parameter of inflation,
was brought about by increases observed in the indices of all
main groups except clothing and footwear, it said in a statement
here.
</P>
<P>
The index for food increased by 5.2 percent while other groups
which had a high increase in their indices included beverages and
tobacco (9.7 percent), medical care and health expenses (3.6
percent) and recreation, entertainment, education and cultural
services (3.4 percent), the statistics show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
