<DOCNO> XIE19990816.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Crushes Eritrea 4-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe blanketed Eriteria for a
4-0 victory in an African Cup of Nations qualifying match on
Sunday in Harare.
</P>
<P>
Sawu scored the goals in the 68th, 73rd and 90th minute of the
game after Adam Ndlovu had opened the scoring at the 61st minute.
</P>
<P>
The win by Zimbabwe was described by coach Clemens Westerhof as
a major step towards qualifying for the African Nations Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
The coach said Zimbabwe's chances were bright but were now
hanging on Eriteria beating or drawing with Senegal in the last
match of the round robin qualifying matches next Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe now is in top position with nine points and Senegal is
the second with six points.
</P>
<P>
It is, however, likely that the qualifying group would be
decided on goal difference as analysts are predicating that
Senegal would beat Eriteria who they walloped by six goals to two
in the reverse match.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe, Eriteria and Senegal were placed in a round robin
group for the African Cups of Nations Qualifiers after the
Confederation of African Football stripped Zimbabwe of hosting the
finals citing poor facilities.
</P>
<P>
The finals would be jointly hosted by Ghana and Nigeria early
next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
