<HEADLINE> Brembilla Wins 1,500 Meters Freestyle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Former European champion Emiliano
Brembilla of Italy took the 1,500 meters freestyle in the swimming
competition at the Military World Games here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"I did not believe I was able to finish the race in such a good
time because it was quite hard to change in 10 minutes from 200
meters to 1,500," said Brembilla, who was second behind Dragos
Coman of Romania in the 200 meters event.
</P>
<P>
He took sweet revenge in the 1,500 meters, clocking 15 minutes
27.58. Istanbul European Championships runner-up Coman this time
came in second in 15:32.19.
</P>
<P>
Both China's Qi Hui and Shan Ying won their third gold medal
when they won the women's 4x100 meters medley relay along with
teammates He Cihong and Qu Yun.
</P>
<P>
Russia took the men's title, beating Ukraine to second place.
Hosts Croatia was third.
</P>
<P>
France's Jean-Cristophe Sarnin, also runner-up in Istanbul,
took the men's 200 meters breaststroke while Russia's Sutyagina
Natalya won the women's 100 meters butterfly.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine's Svitlana Bondarenko, another silver medalist in
Istanbul, edged Qi to second place to win the women's 100 meters
breaststroke.
</P>
<P>
She timed 1:08.88 ahead of Qi in 1:09.15, setting a military
record.
</P>
<P>
Bondarenko said this fulfilled her wish before coming to Zagreb.
</P>
<P>
"One of my goals before coming to these games had been set a
new International Military Sports Council record in this event...
I am free to say now that my coming to Croatia was a great success.
" 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
