<HEADLINE> Russia Overtakes China on Medals Table </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
By sportswriter Cao Li
</P>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Russia overtook China to lead the
medals table here on Sunday as the Military World Games was
nearing its end.
</P>
<P>
Russia collected five golds even before the day's competition
was over while China pocketed two golds on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Russia now had at least 31 gold medals while China had 28.
</P>
<P>
The Russians struck double golds in athletics, had two golds in
swimming and one from men's center fire pistol rapid fire in
shooting.
</P>
<P>
One of China's gold medals of Sunday came from women's 4x100
meters medley relay and the other women's obstacle run relay in
military pentathlon.
</P>
<P>
China's Shan Ying and Qi Hui won their third gold medal after
the medley victories.
</P>
<P>
Shan said after the medal ceremony: "For the third time I am
descending from the podium. You know it isn't that bad at all up
there." 
