<HEADLINE> Celestino Surprise Winner in Cycling World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Mirko Celestino surprised
his opponents by scoring his first major victory Sunday in the
cycling World Cup in Hamburg.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Celestino, who turned professional in 1996,
finished the 251 kilometers in six hours 20.39 minutes, while
Germany's Raphael Sweda was second followed by Latvia's Roman
Vainsteins.
</P>
<P>
The stiffing wind and heavy rainbursts had forced some
favorites, such as France's Christophe Moreau vom Festina-Team who
crashed out the course and Telekom's Jan Ullrich finished far back
in the pack.
</P>
<P>
Belgium's Andrei Tchmil finished with the pack 19 seconds
behind to retain the overall lead in the World Cup standings.
</P>
</TEXT>
