<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sampras Beats Rafter to Win ATP Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- World No. 1 Pete Sampras of
the United States beat world No. 2 Patrick Rafter of Australia 7-6
(9-7), 6-3 Sunday to win the $2.45 million ATP Championship for
his 60th tournament title in Mason, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who has won 22 consecutive matches and four
tournaments this year, served 12 aces, landing 67 percent of his
first serves.
</P>
<P>
"From the first couple of games, I felt like my rhythm was
there," Sampras said. "I felt I was hitting big, and I was hitting
close to the line."
</P>
<P>
Sampras said he was surprised that so many of his serves were
clocked over 130 mph. "We played at a time when it was hot and dry
and the ball was going through the air very quick," Sampras said
of the early evening match. "Two guys who serve and volley very
well on a quick court with really quick conditions and balls, I
think we both were struggling to return serve."
</P>
<P>
Sampras is 9-4 against Rafter, but Rafter had beaten Sampras
three straight times.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, who has won the past two U.S. Opens, received treatment
for his shoulder during and after the match and said it would have
to fully mend for him to defend his Open title.
</P>
<P>
After this triumph, Sampras will continue rank as the No. 1
player in ATP Tour points when the new rankings were released
Monday. It will be his record 273rd week at No. 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
